# Licensed / copyrighted third-party material — NEVER commit (policy 2026-07-14).
# These are non-redistributable (FAIR Institute CC-BY-NC-ND, licensed reports,
# datasets); keep local-only, each team member fetches their own copy. The prior
# patterns missed the docs/reference/ variants that got committed — both actual
# tracked paths are pinned below. Belt-and-suspenders enforcement = the licensed-
# pattern denylist gate (#555 PR1).
docs/reference/Cyenthia Reports/
docs/reference/Data Breach Dataset.csv
docs/reference/FAIR Institute -- Cyber Risk Scenario Taxonomy (February 2025).pdf
docs/reference/fair-scenario-taxonomy.pdf
docs/CIS 8.0 to FAIR-CAM Mapping V1.0.xlsx
docs/FAIR Controls Analytics Model (FAIR-CAM) Standard V1.0 (January 2025).pdf
docs/NIST CSF 1.1 to FAIR-CAM 1.0 Mapping_Final.xlsx
docs/reference/NIST CSF 1.1 to FAIR-CAM 1.0 Mapping_Final.xlsx

# Competitive landscape research drafts — local-only working notes;
# not committed because they're personal scratch, not project artifacts.
docs/reference/competitive-oss-crq-2026-05-13.md
docs/reference/competitive-safe-crq-2026-05-11.md

