# UAT-time artifacts (screenshots, generated PDFs, browser captures, ad-hoc
# helper scripts) — local-only by convention. Operators collect these mid-
# UAT to share with reviewers; they're not source of truth.
tests/screenshots/
tests/*.webarchive
tests/idraa-executive-*.pdf
scripts/_uat_screenshot.py

# npm byproducts — package.json is a declaration-only manifest for the
# vendored front-end libs (see its description); there is no Node toolchain.
# If anyone ignores that and runs `npm install`, don't let these get committed.
node_modules/
package-lock.json

# Deployment configuration is operator-local, never tracked in the public
# repo (owner decision 2026-07-23): platform, sizing, and DB-path details
# are deployment disclosures. Keep your fly.toml (or equivalent) beside the
# checkout; the tracked-path denylist enforces this.
fly.toml
fly.*.toml
